Political thugs struck in Ondo State, shooting the campaign team of the candidate of the Social Democratic Party, SDP, Ebenezer Adeniyan, for the Akure South Constituency II seat into the Ondo State House of Assembly.
Adeniyan’s campaign train was attacked, on Friday, at Oke Aro area of Akure, the state capital, during a tour of some wards of the town.
The SDP candidate, also publisher of “Trace News Magazine” on his electioneering campaign to represent Akure South Constituency II in the Ondo State House of Assembly, escaped assassination but the thugs damaged some vehicles while shooting sporadically to disrupt the campaign activities.
